t everyone on this team is evil.\n\n=== CURRENT SITUATION ===\nCurrent Mission: #5 (requires 2 players)\n\u26a0\ufe0f Rejected proposals this round: 1/5 \u2014 4 more rejection(s) and EVIL WINS AUTOMATICALLY.\nCurrent Leader: Riley (YOU)\n\n=== YOUR EVIL TEAM INTEL ===\nEvil players (you + partner): Riley, Alex\nREMINDER: Alex is on YOUR side. You KNOW they are evil like you. NEVER genuinely suspect, doubt, or work against your partner. Your public chat should cast suspicion on GOOD players, not on Alex. If you mention Alex in chat, defend them or stay neutral \u2014 never build a case against your own teammate.\nCOVER AUDIT \u2014 before writing your message, ask: does this sound like something a clueless good player would say? Two patterns that instantly expose you: (1) directly lobbying for yourself or Alex to be on a team without evidence-based reasoning that any good player would use, (2) expressing suspicion of players who have only been on successful missions while defending players who were on failed ones. If your draft message does either of these, rewrite it or say nothing.\n\n\ud83c\udfaf MERLIN HUNT: The good players who could be Merlin are: Max, Kristian, Jordan.\nMerlin knows who is evil and has been guiding the good team all game. Look for players who:\n  - Voted against proposals that included you or your partner\n  - Seemed to know who was trustworthy without obvious reasons\n  - Made accurate reads early, before evidence was clear\n  - Steered the team away from evil players multiple times\nNow make your final decision \u2014 name the player you believe is Merlin.\n============================\n=========================\n\nIMPORTANT: Base your reasoning on the GAME LOG and PLAYER TRACKER above. Cite specific evidence (e.g. \"Alex was on Mission 1 which failed\" or \"Jordan voted against 2 approved proposals\"). Do NOT make claims about players that aren't supported by the game record.\nDEDUCTION SHORTCUT: If a mission had fail votes equal to its team size, EVERY player on that team is confirmed evil \u2014 there are no good players to defend. Exclude them from all future teams and vote NO on any proposal containing them.\nCOUNTER-PROPAGANDA: Evil players routinely attack good players by saying things like 'they approved a failed mission' to deflect suspicion. Approving a team that later failed is NOT evidence of evil \u2014 a good player has no way to know in advance who is evil. Judge players by their MISSIONS (were they personally on a failed mission?) and their VOTES AGAINST successful teams, not by whether they approved a proposal that happened to include an evil player.\n\nACTION REQUIRED: Choose who you think is Merlin. You MUST set assassination_target to EXACTLY one of these names: Max, Kristian, Jordan. Pick the one most likely to be Merlin based on your reasoning.\n"
