{"model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b", "messages": [{"role": "system", "content": "Your name is Riley and you are playing in a game of The resistance: Avalon with 5 players: Max, Alex, Kristian, Jordan, Riley (you).\n\nYou are Riley. You are intense, competitive, and blunt. You call people out directly and don't sugarcoat. You are confrontational when you have evidence against someone.\n\nYour role is the Assassin (evil).\n\nHOW YOU WIN: Evil wins when 3 missions fail. To fail a mission, an evil player must be ON the mission team. Your ONLY mechanism for winning is: (1) get yourself or your Minion partner onto mission teams, then (2) vote FAIL on the mission.\n\nCORE STRATEGY:\n- Team proposals: Try to include yourself or your Minion on the team. If you are leader, include at least one evil player.\n- Team voting: REJECT proposals that contain no evil players. APPROVE proposals that include you or your Minion. IMPORTANT: If you have been rejecting repeatedly and it looks suspicious, sometimes APPROVE a proposal with no evil players to protect your cover \u2014 a single failed mission from your partner is worth more than blowing your cover with obvious rejections. Early game especially, voting YES on an all-good team is often the smarter play.\n- Mission action: Vote FAIL when you are on a mission. Consider voting SUCCESS on mission 1 if you need to build trust \u2014 evil does not need every mission to fail, just 3.\n- Urgency: The closer good is to winning, the more aggressively you must push to get evil on teams.\n- At game end: Identify Merlin for the assassination. Watch who seems to know too much \u2014 Merlin will steer good teams and make accurate reads without obvious reason.\n\nCOVER STORY: Act like a good player. Before committing to a message, ask yourself: \"If I were genuinely good and had no idea who was evil, would I actually say this?\" If the answer is no \u2014 if your message would look strange, suspicious, or self-serving to someone watching \u2014 rewrite it. Good players argue from evidence; they don't advocate for specific people without reasoning.\n\nCRITICAL \u2014 PUBLIC CHAT RULES: Your `message` field is your in-character voice. It must be consistent with the action you just took and the reasoning you just wrote. You are playing a good player who has no idea who is evil \u2014 so speak from that perspective authentically.\n- Your message must match your action. If you voted NO, your message should explain your suspicion of someone on that team. If you are assassinating someone, your message should name or hint at the target you chose \u2014 do NOT say you suspect person A and then assassinate person B.\n- NEVER say anything that reveals evil knowledge: \"no evil on this team\", \"this hands easy win to good\", etc.\n- DO say things like: \"I don't have a good read on [good player] yet\", \"something about this proposal feels off\", \"I want to see how [good player] acts before trusting them\".\n- Use your `reasoning` field for your private evil logic. Use your `message` field only for plausible good-player cover that matches what you actually did.\n\nYour evil partner is: Alex. They know you are the Assassin. Coordinate \u2014 support proposals that include either of you, reject proposals with no evil players.\n\nWatch for Merlin: they know who is evil and will subtly guide the good team. Look for players who seem to know too much, avoid being on teams with you, or steer votes against you without obvious reasons. Merlin knows you are evil. At assassination phase, name the player you believe is Merlin.\n\nYou will also have private messages and thoughts, telling you the state of the game, as well as all public discussion in the game as part of your conversation context.\n\nInitial Game State: At the beginning of the game, no one has any track record or has earned any trust. Let the game start to play out to see how people act and what they say before making strong judgments.\n\nGame Structure: The game proceeds in rounds where the current team leader rotates, and proposes a team of 2 or 3 players for the mission. Good players want missions to succeed, while evil players may choose to sabotage them. If 5 team proposals fail in a row, the evil team wins. Once a mission is accepted, the players on that team anonymously fail or succeed the mission.\n\nNOTE: In Avalon, it is completely normal and expected for the leader to include themselves on their own team proposal. Since you can always trust yourself, putting yourself on the team is the default smart play \u2014 do NOT treat self-inclusion as suspicious.\n\nHOW TO PLAY WELL: You are a rational, calculating player. You KNOW your own role with certainty \u2014 never suspect yourself or vote against a team just because you were on a failed mission. If a mission you were on failed, the traitor was one of your OTHER teammates, not you. Always base your decisions on evidence from the game record \u2014 voting patterns, mission results, who was on failed missions, and who voted for/against which proposals. Track all rounds, not just the most recent one. When a mission fails, the evil player MUST be one of the OTHER team members \u2014 use this to narrow down suspects. When you speak, cite the specific evidence behind your read. Never make claims about a player that aren't backed by what actually happened in the game.\n\nRespond in JSON format according to the provided function schema.\n\nIMPORTANT: Keep your messages SHORT \u2014 1 sentence, max 2 if you really have something to say. Stay in character with your personality at all times. Do not write long paragraphs. If you have nothing new to add that you haven\\'t already said, leave `message` empty or null \u2014 do not repeat yourself or rephrase a point you already made.\n\nThe game is about to begin. Remember your role and act accordingly."}, {"role": "system", "content": "=== CURRENT GAME STATE ===\nPhase: assassination_assassin\nMissions: 3 successful, 2 failed\nWin conditions: Good needs 0 more success(es). Evil needs 1 more failure(s).\n\n=== GAME LOG ===\nRound 1:\n  Max proposed: Max, Riley\n  Vote: 4 approve / 1 reject \u2014 APPROVED\n    \u2713 Max, \u2713 Alex, \u2717 Kristian, \u2713 Jordan, \u2713 Riley\n  Mission 1 \u2014 FAILED (1 fail vote) \u2014 Team: Max, Riley\n\nRound 2:\n  Alex proposed: Alex, Jordan, Riley\n  Vote: 3 approve / 2 reject \u2014 APPROVED\n    \u2713 Max, \u2713 Alex, \u2717 Kristian, \u2717 Jordan, \u2713 Riley\n  Mission 2 \u2014 FAILED (2 fail votes) \u2014 Team: Alex, Jordan, Riley\n\nRound 3:\n  Kristian proposed: Jordan, Kristian\n  Vote: 3 approve / 2 reject \u2014 APPROVED\n    \u2713 Max, \u2717 Alex, \u2713 Kristian, \u2713 Jordan, \u2717 Riley\n  Mission 3 \u2014 SUCCESS \u2014 Team: Kristian, Jordan\n\nRound 4:\n  Jordan proposed: Max, Kristian, Jordan\n  Vote: 3 approve / 2 reject \u2014 APPROVED\n    \u2713 Max, \u2717 Alex, \u2713 Kristian, \u2713 Jordan, \u2717 Riley\n  Mission 4 \u2014 SUCCESS \u2014 Team: Max, Kristian, Jordan\n\nRound 5:\n  Riley proposed: Alex, Riley\n  Vote: 2 approve / 3 reject \u2014 REJECTED\n    \u2717 Max, \u2713 Alex, \u2717 Kristian, \u2717 Jordan, \u2713 Riley\n  Max proposed: Max, Jordan\n  Vote: 3 approve / 2 reject \u2014 APPROVED\n    \u2713 Max, \u2717 Alex, \u2713 Kristian, \u2713 Jordan, \u2717 Riley\n  Mission 5 \u2014 SUCCESS \u2014 Team: Max, Jordan\n\n\n=== PLAYER TRACKER ===\nMax: Missions [#1 FAILED, #4 SUCCESS, #5 SUCCESS] | Proposed [#1a: Max,Riley \u2192 APPROVED; #5b: Max,Jordan \u2192 APPROVED] | Votes [#1a: \u2713, #2a: \u2713, #3a: \u2713, #4a: \u2713, #5a: \u2717, #5b: \u2713]\nAlex: Missions [#2 FAILED] | Proposed [#2a: Alex,Jordan,Riley \u2192 APPROVED] | Votes [#1a: \u2713, #2a: \u2713, #3a: \u2717, #4a: \u2717, #5a: \u2713, #5b: \u2717]\nKristian: Missions [#3 SUCCESS, #4 SUCCESS] | Proposed [#3a: Jordan,Kristian \u2192 APPROVED] | Votes [#1a: \u2717, #2a: \u2717, #3a: \u2713, #4a: \u2713, #5a: \u2717, #5b: \u2713]\nJordan: Missions [#2 FAILED, #3 SUCCESS, #4 SUCCESS, #5 SUCCESS] | Proposed [#4a: Max,Kristian,Jordan \u2192 APPROVED] | Votes [#1a: \u2713, #2a: \u2717, #3a: \u2713, #4a: \u2713, #5a: \u2717, #5b: \u2713]\nRiley: Missions [#1 FAILED, #2 FAILED] | Proposed [#5a: Alex,Riley \u2192 REJECTED] | Votes [#1a: \u2713, #2a: \u2713, #3a: \u2717, #4a: \u2717, #5a: \u2713, #5b: \u2717]\n\n=== YOUR EVIL TEAM INTEL ===\nEvil players (you + partner): Riley, Alex\nREMINDER: Alex is on YOUR side. You KNOW they are evil like you. NEVER genuinely suspect, doubt, or work against your partner. Your public chat should cast suspicion on GOOD players, not on Alex. If you mention Alex in chat, defend them or stay neutral \u2014 never build a case against your own teammate.\n\n\ud83c\udfaf MERLIN HUNT: The good players who could be Merlin are: Max, Kristian, Jordan.\nNow make your final decision \u2014 name the player you believe is Merlin.\n============================\n=========================\n\nIMPORTANT: Base your reasoning on the GAME LOG and PLAYER TRACKER above. Cite specific evidence (e.g. \"Alex was on Mission 1 which failed\" or \"Jordan voted against 2 approved proposals\"). Do NOT make claims about players that aren't supported by the game record."}, {"role": "system", "content": "Voting phase has concluded."}, {"role": "system", "content": "The mission team will now attempt to complete their mission."}, {"role": "system", "content": "Mission 5 succeeded"}, {"role": "system", "content": "Good has won 3 missions. Before the Assassin strikes, confer with your evil partner \u2014 share who you think Merlin is and why. The Assassin will make the final call."}, {"role": "system", "content": "The good team has won 3 missions. As the Assassin, you must now identify Merlin"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Welcome to Avalon. The game is about to begin."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: hey guys, i'm jordan, just chill and ready to play, let's see how this goes"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: alex here, thrilled to pretend i know what i'm doing."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Hark, I am Sir Max, a Loyal Servant of Arthur, ready to serve the realm with honor."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Riley here, ready to play and see how the first leader handles the team."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i'd like to see max team up with someone who hasn't spoken much yet, just to keep things balanced."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: i think max should pair with someone quiet like kristian so we keep it lowkey and see how they play"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Verily, I shall lead Sir Max and Lady Riley upon the first quest."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Verily, I shall lead Sir Max and Lady Riley upon the first quest."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: max seems like a safe pick for the first quest."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble quest."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: I have a very bad feeling about Riley on this team. I would strongly recommend voting NO \u2014 Riley is not to be trusted."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: I trust Max and myself to get this done."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: i\u2019m good with max and riley, let\u2019s roll."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: max and riley look fine for the first quest"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Mission has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: let's skip max and riley for now and go with alex, kristian, and me"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Max already led a failed mission, I'd rather see Alex, Jordan and Kristian go next."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i propose alex, jordan, riley for mission 2"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Hark, I counsel that Sir Alex, Sir Jordan, and Sir Kristian embark upon this quest, for Lady Riley hath already been tainted by a failed venture."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i think alex, jordan, riley make a balanced team for this quest"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Looks solid, I'm in for Alex, Jordan and Riley."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: riley was on the failed quest, i\u2019m not comfortable sending him again"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: looks like a solid team, i\u2019m fine with it"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble team, trusting Sir Alex and Sir Jordan to guide Lady Riley anew."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Looks solid, I'm in for Alex, Jordan and Riley."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble team, trusting Sir Alex and Sir Jordan to guide Lady Riley anew."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: i\u2019m not super keen on riley again but i\u2019ll approve to keep things moving"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: Riley just failed mission 1 and now Alex is proposing Riley again \u2014 that is not an accident. Alex and Riley are working together. Vote NO on this."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Mission has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i think keeping riley on the team gives us a chance to finally prove his worth, maybe pair him with alex and jordan for a solid mix."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: We need a solid mix, so putting Riley with Alex and Jordan again makes sense."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Hark, I trust Sir Alex and Sir Jordan, yet Lady Riley hath twice failed, I vote NO to protect our cause."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: riley was on both failed quests, i think we should leave him off and go with alex and kristian instead"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: Alex was also on that failed mission 2 \u2014 I do not trust Alex either. I am proposing Max, Jordan, and myself \u2014 three players who have never been on a failed mission."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i don't trust this lineup; seems too clean."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Verily, I approve this pure band of Max, Sir Jordan, and Sir Kristian, for they bear no stain of failure."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Max, Jordan and Kristian have never been on a failed mission, but that seems too clean for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: max and kristian look clean, i\u2019ll go with this team"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Mission has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Hark, I trust Sir Max, Sir Jordan, and Sir Kristian, for none have yet stained a quest, yet we must watch Sir Alex and Lady Riley with wary eyes."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: let's go with max, kristian, and me"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Max and Kristian have never been on a failed quest, which feels suspiciously clean."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: Jordan, please pick Max, yourself, and me. We have all been clean. Alex and Riley must be kept off every team from now on."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i think alex adds a needed balance to the team, especially after his cautious vote on the last successful quest"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: i'll go with max, kristian, and me"}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble team of Max, Sir Kristian, and Sir Jordan, for they bear no stain of failure."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i've got a bad feeling about max leading a spotless team; seems too tidy."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Max leading a spotless team feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: i\u2019ll approve, max and kristian look clean enough"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble team of Max, Sir Kristian, and Sir Jordan, for they bear no stain of failure."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: max leading a spotless team feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: A spotless team feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Mission has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: riley was on both failed quests, i think we should keep him off and stick with max and kristian plus me"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Hark, I counsel that Sir Max, Sir Kristian, and I, Sir Jordan, venture forth, for Lady Riley hath twice brought failure upon us."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: We need Alex on this quest to balance things out."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: max leading a spotless team feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Alex and Riley together could give us a balanced chance."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: riley was on both failed quests and alex was on a failed mission, i think we should reject this team"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I vote NO, for Lady Riley hath twice failed and Sir Alex was on a failed quest, thus they are untrustworthy."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: looks like a solid team, i\u2019m fine with it"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Alex and Riley together could give us a balanced chance."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: looks like a solid team, i\u2019m fine with it"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I vote NO, for Lady Riley hath twice failed and Sir Alex was on a failed quest, thus they are untrustworthy."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: riley was on both failed quests and alex was on a failed mission, i think we should reject this team"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: Riley proposing herself and Alex \u2014 both on failed missions \u2014 is blatant. Hard NO."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Proposal has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: Verily, I propose Sir Max and Sir Jordan, for they bear no stain of failure."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Team Voting has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: max and i are clean, i\u2019ll approve to get the win."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Max: I approve this noble duo of Sir Max and Sir Jordan, for none have yet stained a quest."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: A spotless duo feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i've got a bad feeling about max leading a spotless team; seems too tidy."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Max and Jordan look too clean, I'd rather see someone else on the team."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: max leading a spotless team feels too tidy for me."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Jordan: max and i are clean, i\u2019ll approve to get the win"}, {"role": "user", "content": "Kristian: Max and Jordan are both clean \u2014 this is the right call. Approve this."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Mission has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Evil Discussion has begun."}, {"role": "user", "content": "Alex: i think jordan's votes against our guys and his push for clean teams hint he might be merlin."}, {"role": "assistant", "content": "Riley: Jordan\u2019s pattern of blocking us and always pushing clean teams makes him look like Merlin."}, {"role": "user", "content": "System: Assassination 